The paper proposes a novel feature selection method based on determinantal point processes (DPPs) in the context of Bayesian sparse regression. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), spatial statistics (cs.ST), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on feature selection and sparse regression, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of DPPs also suggests a potential connection to probabilistic graphical models (cs.AI) and kernel methods (cs.LG). The applications in bioinformatics and spatial statistics could also suggest cs.BIO and cs.GR as possible sub-categories, but these are less likely given the focus on feature selection and sparse regression.
